summary: At this point, I don’t understand the lack of communication with the phandom, not because they owe us anything, but because it...
question: At this point, I don’t understand the lack of communication with the phandom, not because they owe us anything, but because it just seems kinda odd? Like aren’t they losing money and followers? From a business perspective it just seems like giving us anything would make more sense, and on a more personal note it would be better to tell us about things rather than letting us find out from someone else.. do you think dnp realize what’s happening or do you think it just goes over their heads?
answer:
I think the thing to remember here is that they’re adult people with a full range of awareness about their career, their finances, and their audience.

I guess the one thing I believe above everything else is that this is happening for a reason on their end. I’m not saying the reason has anything to do with us, whatever is going on may have NOTHING to do with us, but the audience is not the end all and be all of their life. I’m not saying this in a cheesy ‘believe in them’ way but just from a basic premise of accepting that we don’t have the full picture - and they do. Just because we don’t know why something happens doesn’t mean there isn’t a reason for it. The problem with ‘from a business perspective’ reasoning is that a) they know their business better than we do, and b) sometimes life things preempt business things. There’s no amount of pointing to other YouTubers or comparing them to other people that obligates Dan and Phil to tell us personal things in their lives. The one constant of them throughout their entire career is that they are an unmovable wall when it comes to telling us things before they’re ready.

I’m also not saying you can’t be mad at them about it. Our perspective is the only one we have. It sucks that the videos stopped. It’s okay to be upset because we want more of their focus on us. But trying to project what you think would ‘fix it’ or guess why they’re doing it is a futile game until they’re ready to share. There are times in your life when doing your job just isn’t the most important thing happening and not what you want most of your focus on, and as much as it may feel unfair to those of us without the luxury - they do have the means to put it on back burner when most of us don’t.

summary: I woke up extra soft for Dan today. I love that dork so much. I love his hyena laugh and his soft “hello”s. And his prayer hands...
body:
I woke up extra soft for Dan today. I love that dork so much. I love his hyena laugh and his soft “hello”s. And his prayer hands when he gets excited. I love that he’s so passionate about being the best possible version of himself. I love that he cares so deeply and gets too invested. I hope he’s still aware of how much he’s loved by the people in this community.



But you bastards better not say anything or tell him that….I have a reputation here!
